Interface MultilateralNettableState<T>

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    NettableState<N,T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Obligation.State

    public MultilateralNettableState<T>

    Interface for state objects that support being netted with other state objects.

    • Constructor Detail

      • MultilateralNettableState

        public MultilateralNettableState()

    • Method Detail

      • getMultilateralNetState

        @NotNull
T getMultilateralNetState()

        Returns an object used to determine if two states can be subject to close-out netting. If two states return equal objects, they can be close out netted together.
